      "id": "entry-002",
      "title": "Card System",
      "content": "## Memory Cards\n\nCards in Echoes of the Void are called **Memories** - fragments of power left behind by those consumed by the Void.\n\n### Card Types\n\n| Type | Color | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| Attack | Red | Deal damage to enemies |\n| Defense | Blue | Block incoming damage |\n| Skill | Green | Utility effects, buffs, debuffs |\n| Void | Purple | High risk, high reward corrupted cards |\n| Artifact | Gold | Permanent passive effects |\n\n### Rarity Tiers\n\n- **Common** - Basic effects, easy to find\n- **Uncommon** - Stronger effects, moderate rarity\n- **Rare** - Build-defining powerful cards\n- **Void-Touched** - Corrupted variants with enhanced but dangerous effects\n\n### Memory Bonds\n\nWhen two cards are played consecutively 5+ times in a run, they form a **Memory Bond**. Bonded cards:\n- Cost 1 less energy when played after their bonded partner\n- Gain visual particle effects showing their connection\n- Can unlock special combo effects in later updates",
      "tags": ["design", "cards", "mechanics"],
      "createdAt": "2026-01-16T09:00:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-01-30T11:15:00Z"
    },
