      "id": "entry-003",
      "title": "Combat Flow",
      "content": "## Turn Structure\n\n### Player Phase\n1. Draw 5 cards (modified by relics/effects)\n2. Gain 3 Energy (base amount)\n3. Play cards from hand\n4. Discard remaining cards\n5. End turn\n\n### Enemy Phase\n1. Execute telegraphed intent\n2. Apply status effects\n3. Advance Void Meter if applicable\n\n## The Void Meter\n\nA global threat mechanic unique to our game:\n\n- Fills slightly each turn (base: 5%)\n- Certain cards/events increase it faster\n- At 100%, a **Void Surge** occurs:\n  - All enemies gain +50% damage for 2 turns\n  - Player draws 1 fewer card\n  - Meter resets to 0\n\nManaging the Void Meter adds strategic depth beyond just winning individual fights.\n\n## Damage Calculation\n\n```\nFinal Damage = (Base Damage + Strength) Ã— Multipliers - Block\n```\n\nStatus effects apply before block calculation.",
      "tags": ["design", "combat", "mechanics"],
      "createdAt": "2026-01-17T14:00:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-02-01T09:45:00Z"
    },
